\f0\i0  He dismissed the ruin feeds. "Focus on the forest feed. The mobile one." The feed stabilized, panning across the clearing. Then it settled on her. Anya. Working beneath the ancient tree, brow furrowed, hands moving with quiet precision.\
He didn't know why, but the sight of her, the sheer contrast with everything he knew, hit him with the force of a physical blow. He felt an immediate, powerful, inexplicable connection. "K-V," he commanded, his voice hushed, intense. "Isolate 
\f2\i that
\f0\i0  feed. Lock onto its signature. Stabilize and enhance. Maximum priority." He leaned forward, utterly captivated, the original purpose of his experiment momentarily forgotten, replaced by the overwhelming mystery of the girl on the screen.\

\f1\b Scene 12: Watching Anya
