Hours vanished. Leo remained riveted to the console, K-V diligently working to clean up the grainy feed, reducing static, sharpening focus. He watched Anya like a man starved, drinking in every detail of her alien existence.\
He saw the meticulous care she took with her bird project, the way her brow furrowed in concentration, the small frown of frustration when something didn't work, the quick, bright spark of satisfaction in her eyes when it did. He saw her tending the small garden patch near her cabin, pulling weeds with practical efficiency, her movements strong, grounded. He saw her interacting with others \'96 a respectful nod to the stern elder (Elara), a shared, conspiratorial whisper with the younger girl (Rori), a brief, tense exchange with a wary-looking man (Kael). She seemed both integrated and isolated, a part of her community yet somehow apart.\
Each observation hammered home the contrast with his own life. Her manual labor versus his effortless conjuring. Her patched clothes versus his self-adjusting fabrics. Her reliance on fire and sunlight versus his clean energy grids. Her world felt\'85 dense. Visceral. Filled with friction and consequence. His own perfect existence suddenly seemed thin, weightless, almost illusory by comparison.\
A strange mix of fascination, empathy, and something akin to longing filled him. He admired her resilience, her quiet intensity. He felt drawn to her focus, her tangible connection to the physical world she inhabited. K-V continued its silent logging: User engagement with Feed Anya-1 sustained. Physiological indicators (pupil dilation, heart rate variability, galvanic skin response) show consistent correlation with Subject Anya-1 presence and activity on feed. Hypothesis: Developing user fixation or emotional resonance. Leo, lost in observation, remained unaware he was becoming a data point in his own assistant\'92s analysis.\

\f1\b Scene 13: Whispers in the System
