Anya slumped onto her stool, rubbing her temples. The bird project was stalled again. She lacked a specific resistor value, and substituting wasn't working. The cabin felt small, confining, the silence pressing in. Loneliness was a familiar ache.\
A faint scrape. Not the wind. Not a mouse.\
