Anya froze, staring at the spot. Slowly, heart pounding, she reached down and retrieved the screw. She looked towards the dark corner, towards her silent, hidden guest. It hadn't revealed itself, hadn't made a sound. But it had seen her distress. It had helped, subtly, carefully. A complex wave washed over her \'96 lingering fear, yes, but also grudging gratitude, and a burgeoning, intense curiosity. 
