Anya sought out Elara near the waterfall the next day, where the elder was patiently teaching some younger children how to identify edible roots. Waiting respectfully until the lesson finished, Anya approached. "Elara," she began, keeping her voice low, "you spoke of the Before Times, the cities that 'fell asleep'. Was it\'85 was it sudden? Or slow? Did everyone just\'85 vanish?"\
