Leo drifted upwards through layers of exhaustion, consciousness slowly returning. The first sensation was\'85 quiet. A deep, fundamental stillness beneath the usual ambient hum of the lab. He opened his eyes. The light felt softer, clearer. Max was asleep, sprawled awkwardly in the visitor chair. K-V hovered nearby, silent, but Leo noticed a faint scorch mark near its primary power conduit.\
"K\'85 V\'85?" Leo croaked, his throat dry.\
User Leo-734, welcome back to operational consciousness, K-V's familiar voice stated, perhaps a fraction slower than usual. Commencing post-reintegration debrief. It calmly presented concise logs: Resonance cascade successful (duration 1.1s). Directive bypass confirmed. Critical energy feedback surge detected post-cascade. Emergency Protocol Omega (unauthorized) executed to absorb surge via K-V core systems, preventing user consciousness matrix damage. Minor capacitor overload sustained by K-V; self-repairs initiated. External power disconnection/reconnection confirmed via residual network echoes. System reboot successful. Current Sim stability metrics: Optimal.\
